South of Asheville / Mile Marker 32 to 34 Both Directions. I-26 in both directions between MM 32 and 34 will&nbsp;be&nbsp;reduced to a single lane&nbsp;while crews work to place steel girders for the NC191 Bridge over I-26. The lane closures will begin at approximately MM34 in the&nbsp;westbound direction and 32 headed East. Lane closures will remain in place through overnight hours while crew complete work over and along&nbsp;travel lanes. Work will begin Sunday night and continue until Monday morning between the hours of&nbsp;7:00 pm and&nbsp;6:00 am.&nbsp;Between the hours of 12 am&nbsp;and 5 am on these days all lanes of I-26 may be stopped for up to 30 mins while crews lift and secure steel beams into place. Additionally between the hours of 10:00PM and 5:00AM exit 33 off I-26 eastbound will be closed and a detour will be in place. Project is under contract with Blythe Development Company.
